  <!-- More Project Information -->
  <name>Rupy</name>
  <description>
    Weighing roughly 45KB, rupy is probably the smallest Java NIO HTTP server in the world. Rupy is inherently non-blocking asynchronous, which makes it the
    ideal candidate for high concurrency real-time applications serving dynamic data. Tested with acme, rupy performs on average ~1300 requests per second
    (RPS). To put that figure in perspective; acme doesn't use keep-alive, so that means 1300 unique TCP connections serving dynamic content per second! Thanks
    to NIO and an event queue to avoid selector trashing, this figure degrades gracefully under high concurrency.
  </description>
